products.name: French Connection / European Oak St. Tropez
products.description: From pastoral countrysides to bustling Parisian streets, a rich history of romance in the modern world comes alive with French Connection. Made exclusively from European Oak, this collection offers a broad spectrum of stunning colors in both Oil and Urethane with Aluminum Oxide finishes. With balanced seven-inch widths, exceptionally thick 4mm wear layers micro-beveled edges, and a variety of different textures, each color achieves a natural, yet luxe look that is as beautiful as any French love story.Please note: The beauty of hardwood flooring lies in natural variations in color, grain, and texture inherent in all wood products. In addition, although we color calibrate all of our photos, colors may appear differently on different monitors and devices and flooring will vary in hue and saturation based on differing lighting conditions. Please expect variation in all flooring. We highly recommend seeing a sample board of flooring in person before making your decision, and understanding that flooring may vary slightly from these boards. Please contact us for more information and to be connected to a sales representative who will point you in the right direction.

details.Warranty: Residential: Limited Lifetime Structure, Limited 25 Year Finish | Commercial: Limited 10 Year Structure, Limited 5 Year Finish

products.name: French Connection / European Oak Caffe Herringbone
products.description: Caffe – one of our most popular and sought after colors – is now available as in-stock herringbone patterned flooring option! Available in 5″ wide by 24-1/16″ length, the thickness, wear layer, and all other specifications are the same as French Connection Caffe plank flooring, allowing you to create a stunning all-herringbone design or mix and match for features and accents!This rich brown color is one of our most popular hardwood flooring colors featuring an eco-friendly oil finish and hand-distressed, wire-brushed face treatment for a natural, vintage-inspired look.  Made exclusively from live sawn European white oak, these exceptional planks are engineered with a thick wear layer and micro-beveled edges. Lush as the French countryside, elegant as a Parisian apartment, and as modern as the St. Tropez boardwalk – fall in love with the French Connection.Please note: The beauty of hardwood flooring lies in natural variations in color, grain, and texture inherent in all wood products.
